content:
{
  "narration": "The narrow entrance to Prisoner's Hold is damp and shadowed, framed by slick stones and gnarled roots twisting from the earth. A faint, musty scent hangs in the cold air, the silence broken only by the distant call of a crow. The clearing is empty except for the scattered remnants of discarded rope and a broken lantern, evidence of hurried activity not long ago.\n\nYou call out softly, \"See anything, Sila?\" But then remember that only you and Kira are present--Sila remains behind at Trader's Rest, out of sight and safely among the other merchants. As you scan the area, Kira steps forward, her elven eyes narrowing as she surveys the floor and the brush beyond the entrance.\n\n\"There's no sign of Sila here, Eirik,\" she says quietly. \"But look--the trail we followed leads right up to this stone outcrop.\" She points to faint drag marks in the mud, then crouches to examine them. \"Someone was definitely here recently. Whatever they dragged, it was heavy, and they were in a hurry. No fresh footprints leading back out yet.\"\n\nThe path ahead curves into gloom, vanishing into the deeper shadows of the Hold. Bits of torn fabric and splinters of wood suggest something was forced through in haste.\n\nKira glances back at you, her voice low. \"Want me to scout ahead, or shall we investigate the marks together? Or do you want to prepare yourself before heading deeper in? The place gives me a bad feeling.\"",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "You grip your shield more tightly, feeling the familiar weight settle comfortably on your arm, and ready your mace, the steel head glinting in the meager light. Kira nods approvingly, drawing her longbow and nocking an arrow with practiced grace. Her eyes never leave the darkened passage ahead as she whispers, \"Agreed. No sense splitting up with trouble this close. I'll cover your left. If anything stirs, I'll spot it.\"\n\nTogether, you move forward into the heart of Prisoner's Hold. The scrape of your boots and the soft pad of Kira's steps echo off the damp, stone walls. The heavy iron bars of the cell loom ahead, behind which sits Rusk, the captured bandit leader. He leans forward on his bench, lips curling in a slow, mocking smile as he sees you approach. \"Well, well. Looks like someone's come to keep me company. What is it today? Mercy, threats, or just more questions?\"\n\nThe nervous rangers stationed at the guard post eye you and Kira with a mixture of relief and wariness, glad not to be alone with Rusk for too long. The evidence lockbox sits on a sturdy table nearby, its steel hasp freshly sealed.\n\nKira gives you a sidelong glance, her voice just above a whisper. \"Do you want to talk to him first, or should I try reading his body language while you question him? Something about his eyes... Makes my skin crawl.\"",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 3
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Kira answers before you even finish your question, her voice steady but wary. \"He's behind those bars, all right. The cell is reinforced, and the guards keep the door locked whenever anyone's inside. Not the most comfortable place, but after what he's done, I can't say I pity him.\"\n\nYou take a closer look: Rusk is indeed confined behind a heavy iron-barred cell at the far end of the cave. Chains bind his wrists and ankles, further limiting his movement. Despite this, he sits with surprising composure, his back straight, scarred hands resting calmly on his knees as if he owns the cell. His eyes flick from Kira to you, sharp and assessing.\n\nA ranger at the guard post quietly confirms, \"Prisoner's secure, sir. Gate's locked and triple-checked. Only way in or out is with the captain's key.\"\n\nRusk lets out a humorless chuckle. \"Oh, they've got me trussed up like a festival hog, priest. But chains don't stop a good story, do they? Or a desperate man from making a deal. So... which are you here for? Justice, confession, or negotiation?\"",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}
